Miami_Gardens.WAMI-DT: WAMI-DT, virtual channel 69 (UHF digital channel 47), is a UniMás owned-and-operated television station licensed to Hollywood, Florida, United States and serving Miami and Fort Lauderdale. It is one of two East Coast flagship stations of the Spanish-language network (the other being WFUT-DT in the New York City market). WAMI is owned by the Univision Local Media subsidiary of Univision Communications as part of a duopoly with Miami-licensed Univision flagship WLTV-DT (channel 23).
